# Project Structure and Organization Rules

## For AI Agent

### Directory Structure
- Follow existing project structure: `packages/react/src/`
- Core functionality: `core/` directory
- Utilities: `utils/` directory
- Hooks: `hooks/` directory
- Higher Order Components: `hocs/` directory
- Tests: `__tests__/` directory
- Client entry: `client/` directory

### File Organization
- One primary export per file when possible
- Group related functionality together
- Keep files focused on a single responsibility
- Use index files for clean exports
- Match file names to their primary export

### Import Organization
- Group imports: external libraries, then internal modules
- Use absolute imports from `src/` when configured
- Use relative imports for closely related files
- Import types using `import type` syntax
- Remove unused imports

### Module Exports
- Use named exports for utilities and functions
- Use default exports sparingly (mainly for components)
- Export types and interfaces for reuse
- Create index files to re-export from subdirectories
- Keep exports minimal - only export what's needed

### Code Organization Within Files
- Imports at the top
- Type definitions and interfaces
- Constants
- Utility functions
- Main functions/exports
- Keep related code together

### Project-Specific Patterns
- Follow Mini React implementation patterns
- Maintain separation: core rendering, hooks, HOCs, utilities
- Keep VNode, Instance, Context types in `core/types.ts`
- Keep constants in `core/constants.ts`
- Keep validators in `utils/validators.ts`

### File Naming
- Use kebab-case for file names: `create-element.ts`
- Match file name to primary function/type when possible
- Use descriptive names that indicate file purpose
- Test files: `*.test.ts` or `*.test.tsx`

### Example Structure
```
packages/react/src/
  core/
    constants.ts      # Shared constants
    types.ts          # Type definitions
    context.ts        # Context management
    elements.ts       # VNode creation
    dom.ts            # DOM operations
    reconciler.ts     # Reconciliation logic
    hooks.ts          # Basic hooks
    render.ts         # Rendering logic
    setup.ts          # Setup functions
    index.ts          # Core exports
  hooks/
    useRef.ts
    useMemo.ts
    useCallback.ts
    index.ts
  hocs/
    memo.ts
    deepMemo.ts
    index.ts
  utils/
    validators.ts
    equals.ts
    enqueue.ts
    index.ts
  __tests__/
    basic.mini-react.test.tsx
    advanced.hooks.test.tsx
```

